# Use a hoisted (npm-style) node_modules instead of pnpm's default symlinked
# layout.
#
# Why: Next.js output-file tracing pulls the @remotion/compositor-linux-x64-gnu
# binary into the /api/video/render serverless function (see the globs in
# apps/web/next.config.ts). Under pnpm's default isolated linker those
# node_modules paths are symlinks into .pnpm, and Vercel rejects a function
# package that contains symlinked directories ("invalid deployment package").
# A hoisted layout makes them real files, which traces and deploys cleanly —
# while still keeping each app's binaries (next, tsc, sanity) resolvable.
#
# NOTE: do NOT add `shamefully-hoist=true` here. It hoists every package to the
# repo-root node_modules, which breaks per-app bin resolution on Vercel
# (`next build` → "Cannot find module .../apps/web/node_modules/next/...").
node-linker=hoisted
